\fs44 Regen Studio\'92s Expertise: Living Lab Scheveningen\cb1 \

\fs32 \cb2 \

\fs36 \cb2 \strokec3 Regen Studio has extensive experience working on cutting-edge energy projects, including our involvement in the{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://smartcity.denhaag.nl/en/"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb2 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4  
\f1\b Living Lab Scheveningen}}\'a0with the 
\f1\b City of The Hague
\f0\b0 . This initiative, which explores the potential of smart grid systems in the harbour area at the beach, aims to create a sustainable local energy ecosystem by integrating renewable energy, energy storage, and intelligent energy management. The project showcases how decentralized energy generation, local storage, and a flexible grid can work together to improve energy security and sustainability in urban environments.\cb1 \strokec3 \

\fs32 \cb2 \

\fs36 \cb1 \

\fs32 \cb2 \

\fs36 \cb2 \strokec3 Regen Studio has helped the project design the community, onboard the distribution company, sketch the required technical system, form the project proposals, designed the legal structure of the co\'f6perative, filed the funding requests and started the procurement of the open-source energy management system.\cb1 \strokec3 \

\fs32 \cb2 \

\fs36 \cb1 \

\fs32 \cb2 \

\fs36 \cb2 \strokec3 Through our work in Scheveningen, we have helped demonstrate how smart grids can operate in complex, real-world environments. Our experience in this project has strengthened our expertise in designing scalable, future-proof energy systems that can be adapted to meet the unique needs of any community or business.\cb1 \strokec3 \
